snippet: Yelena Isinbayeva of Russia won a world title for the first time in nearly four years at the world indoor track and field championships in Istanbul.
abstract: Russian pole-vaulter Yelena Isinbayeva wins gold at world indoor track and field championships.
lead_paragraph: Yelena Isinbayeva of Russia won a world title for the first time in nearly four years at the world indoor track and field championships in Istanbul.

headline.main: No Pole-Vault Record, but the Return of a Champion
